                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="232.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the foundation of every webpage on the internet. It is not a programming language but a markup language used to organize and display content on the web. This chapter introduces students to the fundamentals of HTML and walks them through how to properly structure a website using essential tags. From simple text formatting to embedding images and linking pages, students will learn how to build the skeleton of a fully functional website." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
