                  <Text layoutX="54.0" layoutY="520.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The term &quot;HyperText&quot; refers to text that contains links to other text. This is how the web is interconnected — you click a link on one page and are taken to another. HTML uses the &lt;a&gt; tag to create hyperlinks." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
